benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/customFields/pagination - List custom fields

covered: Valid Request scenarios covered: default parameters, explicit offset/limit, and audit parameter variations (FULL, MINIMAL, NONE).
Empty data scenario covered: no custom fields yields 200 with an empty array.
Pagination and large dataset handling: tests include small to very large datasets, boundary values, and multi-parameter combinations (offset/limit, audit, and partial inputs).
Query parameter validation and security: tests cover invalid offset (negative), invalid limit (zero/negative), invalid audit value, SQL injection attempt, and ignoring extra parameters.
Authorization handling: tests cover missing/invalid authentication token resulting in 401.
Error handling and resilience: tests cover system unavailability (503) and timeouts (504/503).
Regression, compatibility, and accessibility: tests cover regression case (TC22), backward compatibility (TC23), and accessibility/schema conformance (TC24).
Audit information handling: tests verify FULL/MINIMAL/NONE audit details are included or omitted as appropriate (TC03/TC04/TC05).
Edge-case coverage: extreme offsets/limits (TC16) and partial input scenarios (TC17/TC18).
Concurrency coverage: concurrent requests scenario ensures correct subsets (TC21).
gaps: Caching headers and caching behavior not tested (ETag, Cache-Control).
403 Forbidden scenario for insufficient privileges not covered (only 401 tested in TC12).
recommendations: Add rate-limiting tests to verify throttling behavior (429).
Add tests for caching semantics, including ETag and Cache-Control headers and cache validation.
Add 403 Forbidden tests to cover insufficient privileges when authenticated.
Consider additional performance tests under sustained load and verify consistency of error payload structure across error scenarios.
